oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Johnny Cash - Live in The Annex NCO Club - Tape 2
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tape 2 of 3. Recording from tape features Johnny Cash (performer) and June Carter (performer) performing on the Johnny Cash Show on an unknown date. Segment was recorded at the Annex 14 NCO Club in Long Binh, Vietnam.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Johnny Cash; June Cash
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00) I Never Will Marry (June Carter) -- (03:38) Wildwood Flower (June Carter) -- (05:24) Worried Man Blues (June Carter) -- (06:34) June talks about Johnny Cash's new show -- (07:08) Big River (Johnny Cash) -- (08:56) Wreck Of The Old '97 (Johnny Cash) -- (10:57) Johnny Cash talks to the audience and introduces the next tune -- (12:03) Five Feet High And Rising (Johnny Cash) -- (13:51) Tennessee Flat Top Box (Johnny Cash) -- (16:46) Cash thanks the solider's and introduces "Remember the Alamo" -- (17:31) Remember The Alamo (Johnny Cash) -- (20:03) I Still Miss Someone (Johnny Cash) -- (21:46) Cocaine Blues (Johnny Cash) -- (24:39) Johnny Cash introduces the band -- (25:12) Folsom Prison Blues (Johnny Cash) -- (27:35) Orange Blossom Special (Johnny Cash)
